cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on unsupervised learning of deep representations for image clustering, which is a common task in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a recurrent framework for joint learning, which involves optimizing a loss function, indicating that it may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on various image datasets, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
